I thought this recipe was fabulous. I made it just as written. I didn't find it to be too difficult or time consuming because of the number of steps that can be done ahead of time. It's impressive to look at and a nice change from crab cakes. The sauce is great and a much needed addition.

Rating: 4
Great appetizer ... made the suggested Red Onion Marmalade (recipe online) -- wonderful addition and a definite must-do. For a dinner party of 8, I used 1 lb of sea scallops (well-drained and patted dry) and about 1 lb of shrimp ... all other ingredients in the original proportions ..... I chopped both the scallops and shrimp ..... put about 1/4th of this mixture into the processor .... then folded in the remaining and refrigerated. Give this a try -- you'll be glad.

